.TH "PACMAN" 6 "June 2026" "pacman.c"
.SH NAME
pacman \- Pacman clone written in C99
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pacman
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pacman
is a desktop Pacman clone implemented in a single C source file and built on the
sokol platform abstraction headers.
.PP
Guide Pacman through the maze, eat all dots, avoid ghosts, and collect pills to
temporarily turn ghosts vulnerable for bonus points.
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.B Arrow keys / W A S D
Move Pacman.
.TP
.B F
Toggle fullscreen mode.
.TP
.B Esc
Quit (native desktop builds).
.SH GAMEPLAY
The game starts with three lives. A round is cleared after all dots and pills are
eaten. Bonus fruit may appear during a round and awards additional points.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I pacman.c
Main source file.
.TP
.I CMakeLists.txt
Build configuration.
.SH BUILDING
Typical build steps:
.PP
.nf
cmake -S . -B build
cmake --build build
./build/pacman
.fi
.PP
On Linux, OpenGL, X11, and ALSA development headers/libraries are required.
.SH PROJECT
Homepage:
.PP
.I https://github.com/floooh/pacman.c
